ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Would recommend to anyone. It is a good overview of all aspects of engineering and exposes students to new ways of modeling and evaluating systems.

Summary - A course covering interesting subject matter in which you will be exposed to useful software tools that is made far more painful than it needs to be.Unless a student is specifically interested in pursuing a research path relating to MEMS, I would not recommend taking this course.
Interdisciplinary class. Learn a variety of different skills in the course.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course is directly related to my research path, which I why I chose to take it.
It helped me to learn a great deal about computer modeling, creating and improving upon a design concept, and teamwork.
